### likely trouble spots

- move/rename must prevent moving a directory into its own subtree
- recursive delete semantics must be explicit and well-tested
- listing `/` must return mixed entry kinds, not only directories
- import/export logic currently assumes one directory level maps to one category
- `search`, `find`, `ls`, `rm`, `mv`, `reindex` all encode category-era assumptions
- metadata types currently expose `category_name` / `category_id` and will need full path or parent info instead

### implementation order I recommend

1. settle path rules and public naming (`directory`, absolute paths, no ids in paths)
2. replace sqlite schema and storage API around generic entries/tree resolution
3. update search index to subtree-aware filtering
4. update RPC/REST
5. update CLI and shell UX (`mkdir`, `ls`, `mv`, `rm`, flags, help text)
6. rewrite docs and tests together

this is the correct kind of breaking change: one clean cut, not seven ceremonial scratches.

