### BUG 2 — `mv src dst/` silently renames instead of moving into [CRITICAL]

`execute.rs:952–975`

`normalize_mv_segment` strips the trailing `/` from `chats/`. Then both `src=/chat1` and `dst=/chats` have parent `/`, so `sp == dp` → `rename_directory("/chat1", "/chats")`. Since `/chats` already exists → duplicate error. The user's intent — move `/chat1` INTO `/chats` — is never reached.

Fix: if `dst` ends with `/` (or `dst` resolves as an existing directory), treat as "move src into dst, keeping src's final name segment". i.e. destination becomes `{dst}/{src_name}`.

